dc_title_s: Map of the north polar region
dc_description_s: Shows destinations and some routes of arctic explorers 1553-1879.; Contains view: Wrangell Land "as seen from Bark Nile of New London, Capt. Th. Long. Aug 14th 15th & 16th 1867, 15 to 18 miles distant. From U.S. Hydrographic Office chart No. 68."; Selective relief shown by hachures and spot heights.|63 x 78 centimeters|Scale [ca. 1:11,675,000]|General Map Collection
